</div>
</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>La Clusaz, France</h2>
<a name="clusaz"></a>
<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/media/13070088/insiders-guide-best-value-la-clusaz.jpg" alt="Fab 5 Best Value Ski Resorts - La Clusaz" data-udi="umb://media/211abbb4636246359b0aed39aaeb1b34" /></p>
<p>New to Inghams’ programme for this winter, <a data-udi="umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9}" title="La Clusaz"><strong>La Clusaz</strong></a> (1,100m) in the Haute-Savoie region of the French Alps was a small village before it became a ski resort and it has maintained its traditional charm. This means that in-resort prices have remained modest in comparison to more high-profile, glitzy ski resorts.</p>
<p>The 210km ski area is best suited to beginner and intermediate skiers and boarders, with lots of confidence-building runs. And its off-piste terrain shouldn’t be sniffed at either. La Clusaz recently become a big name on the freeriding scene. Mountain restaurants offer affordable lunches: grab a hearty burger or pizza on the terrace of Le Chalet Des Praz from around €12, or tuck in to a ham and cheese crêpe from Le Relais de l’Aiguille for €6.50.</p>
<p>Many of Inghams’ properties, which range from self-catering, to bed and breakfast and half board accommodation, have been selected for their great value. <a data-udi="umb://document/3657e10232fa44bb916d5400c6af5cc0" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3657e10232fa44bb916d5400c6af5cc0}" title="Hotel Alpen Roc"><strong>The Hotel Alpen Roc</strong></a> includes a daily après ski snack and drink, and inclusive drinks with dinner. </p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/597c2d8b93354bef8c187c100894c3f9}" title="La Clusaz"><strong>Find out more about La Clusaz &gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Arinsal, Andorra</h2>
<a name="arinsal"></a>
<p><strong><img src="/media/13070096/insiders-guide-best-value-arinsal-2.jpg" alt="Fab 5 Best Value Ski Resorts Arinsal" data-udi="umb://media/0608aa5ca3bb4b9481cedc1bdf2734ee" /></strong></p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/07c4ee80b2bd4b5c9640b262a5748dd7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/07c4ee80b2bd4b5c9640b262a5748dd7}" title="Arinsal"><strong>Arinsal</strong></a> (1,475m) in <a data-udi="umb://document/043e5aa9497c411db243e21ed0a5049b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/043e5aa9497c411db243e21ed0a5049b}" title="Andorra"><strong>Andorra’s</strong></a> Vallnord Ski Area is well known for its exceptional value for money and arguably Europe’s best-value après ski. Bars often give away FREE snacks and drinks to entice guests in, and printable discount vouchers are available to download from the resort’s website.</p>
<p>Inghams offers two Ski Inclusive Plus hotel options, both of which include a six-day lift pass, six days’ equipment hire, buffet breakfasts and vouchers for lunch on the mountain, as well as FREE wine or beer with evening meals.</p>
<p>FREE ski hosting led by the Inghams Representative is a great way to get to know the 93km of ski terrain, which provides skiers with enviable variety. Arinsal’s skiing is situated in an open snowbowl while its neighbour, Pal has predominantly wooded slopes. A trip to the hidden gem Arcalis (via FREE shuttle bus) is an absolute must for quiet slopes, often excellent snow conditions and great off-piste!</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/07c4ee80b2bd4b5c9640b262a5748dd7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/07c4ee80b2bd4b5c9640b262a5748dd7}" title="Arinsal"><strong>Find out more about Arinsal &gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Livigno, Italy</h2>
<a name="livigno"></a>
<p><img src="/media/13070090/insiders-guide-best-value-livigno.jpg" alt="Fab 5 Best Value Ski Resorts - Livigno" data-udi="umb://media/5b506a2720ae447c92a2bf2dc5b415cd" /></p>
<p>Admittedly, <a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89}" title="Livigno"><strong>Livigno</strong></a> had a reputation as a ‘cheap and cheerful’ ski resort, but recent investment in its hotels and lift system means the Italian resort now caters to more discerning skier, while still maintaining its great value status.</p>
<p>Livigno is a tax-free haven: due to its strategic geographical location - it’s very high (1,820m) and is tucked away on the Swiss border. In 1805 Napoleon made Livigno exempt from excise duties. These privileges continue today, meaning skiers benefit from significantly reduced prices for alcohol, perfumes, cigarettes and tobacco, electronic items, leather garments and high-end goods. The pedestrian centre is lined with lively bars and irresistible duty-free shops.</p>
<p>Skiers and boarders are drawn to Livigno’s plentiful blue and red runs which carve down both sides of the valley (facing east and west), forming a well-positioned ski area with 115km of piste with quality snow at any time of day. Mountain restaurants serving delicious and reasonably-priced Italian cuisine also make for perfect, budget lunchtime stops.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89}" title="Livigno"><strong>Find out more about Livigno &gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>
<p><strong> </strong></p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Les Menuires, France</h2>
<a name="menuires"></a>
<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/media/13070089/insiders-guide-best-value-les-menuires.jpg" alt="Fab 5 Best Value Ski Resorts - Les Menuires" data-udi="umb://media/60ed91db26764cceb4615c39cd6b8130" /></p>
<p>Ski the world-famous <a data-udi="umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578" href="/{localLink:umb://document/72a5198213b1400d8c891f49fe57b578}" title="Three Valleys Ski Area"><strong>Three Valleys</strong></a> for less: stay in the hidden gem resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8}" title="Les Menuires"><strong>Les Menuires</strong></a> (1,815m), nestled within one of Europe’s biggest and best ski areas, at a more affordable price tag. </p>
<p>Les Menuires is a perfect resort for families. Almost all of Inghams’ accommodation is ski-in/ski-out, allowing for stress-free access to the slopes. The fantastically-connected resort attracts skiers of all abilities and it has superb access to the wider ski area (600km).</p>
<p>One of the best value hotel options is the Village Club du Soleil, which offers a FREE six-day lift pass per person and FREE equipment hire, as well as English-speaking children’s clubs and a great entertainment programme. Families can fill up on hearty breakfasts followed by buffet lunches or picnics, saving the need to buy lunch up on the mountain. At dinner time, wine is included, helping parents unwind after a hard day’s skiing.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4eae720ba8984d83a83f530983b4b6f8}" title="Les Menuires"><strong>Find out more about Les Menuires &gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Niederau, Austria</h2>
<a name="niederau"></a>
<p><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="/media/13070092/insiders-guide-best-value-niederau.jpg" alt="Fab 5 Best Value Ski Resorts - Niederau" data-udi="umb://media/93e033c4aa934597813f4b9c837c0690" /></p>
<p>Sitting within the Wildschönau Valley, the classic Tyrolean resort of <a data-udi="umb://document/3c1c4e119772493fa932ed5a06912edf" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3c1c4e119772493fa932ed5a06912edf}" title="Niederau"><strong>Niederau</strong></a> (828m) is a wild and beautiful ski destination. It’s also cheap! A six-day whole area lift pass costs from just £194 per adult in low season and Inghams boasts an excellent selection of great value hotels, as well as flights from a range of UK regional airports, assisting guests in saving on the cost of a taxi ride, airport parking or hotel stay the night before departure.</p>
<p>Wide slopes and excellent ski schools make Niederau an ideal choice for beginner and intermediate skiers and boarders. Guests can also pre-book the Learn to Ski package from £175 per adult, which includes six days’ equipment hire and five days’ tuition.</p>
<p>The Ski Juwel Area (109km) links Niederau with <a data-udi="umb://document/41d9aafa0f294702ba9d5658d85d5583" href="/{localLink:umb://document/41d9aafa0f294702ba9d5658d85d5583}" title="Oberau"><strong>Oberau</strong></a> (via FREE ski bus service), Auffach (home to more challenging slopes) and <a data-udi="umb://document/7cdd4ba75e0044478e4b0e871b159997" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7cdd4ba75e0044478e4b0e871b159997}" title="Alpbach"><strong>Alpbach</strong></a>. Additionally, all guests receive the FREE Wildschönau Card on arrival, which includes guided winter walks and snowshoeing, as well as FREE entry to local museums and discounts on other local activities, helping the holiday budget stretch further.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/3c1c4e119772493fa932ed5a06912edf" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3c1c4e119772493fa932ed5a06912edf}" title="Niederau"><strong>Find out more about Niederau &gt;</strong></a></p>
</div>]]></bodyText>
